title: Grateful Dead Live at Compton Terrace Amphitheatre on 1983-03-25
lineage: MAC > Nakamichi CR-5A > Edirol FA-66 > Wavelab 2448 > CD-Wave (24bit output) > R8Brain > TLH > FLAC 1644 tagged. Transferred by Andrew F. 09/2015
description:
Set 1

Cold Rain & Snow, Minglewood Blues, Dire Wolf, My Brother Esau, Big Railroad Blues, Me & My Uncle-> Big River, Tennessee Jed-> Let It Grow

Set 2

Help On The Way-> Slipknot!-> Franklin's Tower-> Playin' In The Band-> Drums-> Throwing Stones-> Not Fade Away-> Black Peter-> Sugar Magnolia, E: Don't Ease Me In

reviews.review_text:
Compton  Excellent sounding Naks were the best for the Grateful Dead, in your face sound.
Nice run of shows with Brian, Compton, Aladdin,Irving,& Warfield. Speeding ticket and all.
